<task id="034" project="sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>P3 — Fix RB-T050-01: SourcePaneSseEventData.CitationId emit JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull</title>
    <phase>Phase 3: LOW Severity + Integration Stability</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>30-45 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>029</dependencies>
    <blocks>038</blocks>
    <tags>phase-3, bff-api, real-bug-ledger, low-severity, production-fix, sse, serialization</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Production code modification in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SseEventTypes/; FULL rigor required for .cs changes (code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>P3-W1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <production-fix-per-ledger>true</production-fix-per-ledger>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T050-01 by adding `[JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]` to
    `SourcePaneSseEventData.CitationId` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SseEventTypes/SourcePaneSseEvent.cs`. The property currently has
    `JsonPropertyName("citationId")` but no JsonIgnore attribute, so the default writer emits `"citationId": null`
    when the value is null instead of omitting the field.

    Production fix per ledger Proposed Fix section: add the property-level attribute alongside the existing JsonPropertyName:

    ```
    public record SourcePaneSseEventData(
        [property: JsonPropertyName("widgetType")] string WidgetType,
        [property: JsonPropertyName("widgetData")] JsonElement WidgetData,
        [property: JsonPropertyName("citationId")]
        [property: JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]
        string? CitationId = null);
    ```

    Test impact: 1 Skip'd test (`ChatSseEventFactoryTests.CreateSourcePaneEvent_WithNullCitationId_OmitsCitationIdField` Fact) flips Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T050-01" + resolution mode `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `SourcePaneSseEventData.CitationId` (~line 51) decorated with `[JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]`.
    The 1 Skip'd test passes when re-enabled. Ledger row RB-T050-01 → `repaired`. Existing wire-format tests (citationId-present cases)
    continue to pass.
  </goal>

